<article>
    <h1>7 ROAD CASES</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201107/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-07"><time>2020-11-07</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Road cases are my home away from home.</p>
    <p>As soon as I see them at re­hearsals, I get that “Ooh we’re go­ing on tour, this is hap­pen­ing” feel­ing. I love be­ing on tour.</p>
    <p>I love hav­ing that fam­ily at­mos­phere and work­ing with peo­ple who have their own skills. There’s an ad­mi­ra­tion for what ev­ery­one does, whether you’re a light­ing tech­ni­cian, you’re in cater­ing, you’re a dancer, you’re the mon­i­tor guy or woman.</p>
    <p>The way ev­ery­one has to work to­gether.</p>
    <p>I al­ways look for­ward to it, so my road cases are like my friends.</p>
    <p>I just re­alised I might sound like Steve Martin in The Lonely Guy, but it’s not just lonely me and my road cases.</p>
    <p>The re­ally im­por­tant stuff is in there, like cos­tumes, but also my com­forts. I had my road cases made in a soft-pink colour. I wanted ones that would stand out and be mine.</p>


